text:
To create a colorful website with real jokes, you can use HTML and JavaScript to design the layout and display the jokes. Here's a simple example:

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Joke Website</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        .jokes {
            list-style: none;
        }
        .joke {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
        <ul class="jokes">
            <li class="joke">
                <p>Why did the tomato turn red?</p>
                <p>Because it saw the salad dressing!</p>
            </li>
            <li class="joke">
                <p>What do you call a fake noodle?</p>
                <p>An impasta!</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```
JavaScript (optional):
```javascript
// Add smooth scrolling to the page
window.scrollTo(0, 0);
```
This HTML code creates a simple, responsive layout with a white background and a container for the jokes. The JavaScript code adds smooth scrolling to the page when it is loaded. You can replace the two jokes with your own or fetch them from an API.

To create a colorful and interactive website based on the mock-up, you can use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Here's a basic example:

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Joke Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
        <div class="joke-box">
            <div class="joke-type">
                <input type="radio" id="funny-joke" name="joke-type" value="funny" checked>
                <label for="funny-joke">Funny Joke</label>
            </div>
            <div class="joke-type">
                <input type="radio" id="reveal-punchline" name="joke-type" value="reveal-punchline">
                <label for="reveal-punchline">Push to Reveal Punchline?</label>
            </div>
            <div class="joke">
                <p id="joke-text">Enter your joke here</p>
                <button id="submit-joke">Submit Joke</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
CSS:
```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-color: #f2f2f2;
}

.container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
    background-color: #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

.joke-box {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: space-between;
}

.joke-type input[type="radio"] {
    margin-right: 10px;
}

.joke-type label {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 5px;
}

.joke p {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.submit-button {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.submit-button:hover {
    background-color: #45a049;
}
```
JavaScript:
```javascript
const jokeInput = document.getElementById("joke-text");
const submitButton = document.getElementById("submit-joke");
const jokeTypeRadios = document.querySelectorAll("input[name='joke-type']");

submitButton.addEventListener("click", function () {
    if (jokeTypeRadios[0].checked) {
        jokeInput.style.display = "none";
        jokeInput.value = "";
        jokeInput.placeholder = "Enter your funny joke here";
    } else if (jokeTypeRadios[1].checked) {
        jokeInput.style.display = "none";
        jokeInput.value = "";
        jokeInput.placeholder = "Push to reveal punchline?";
    }
});
```
This example creates a simple joke website with a container, joke box, and joke input. The JavaScript code listens for the submit button click event and changes the joke input display and placeholder based on the joke type radio button selected.
